name: Leith Hill - Hiking in London
description:
Join us on our new exciting hike across Surrey's magnificent upland landscapes - designated as an Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty.

Our Surrey Hills exploration will take us through picturesque woodland, heathland and farmland. We will hike to Leith Hill - the second-highest peak in South-East England. Standing at Leith Hill is a majestic tower built in the 18th century which is the highest point in South-East England.

The trails we've chosen will prove the significant landscape value of Surrey, which national importance has been officially recognised since 1958.

Trip Highlights:

• Discover Surrey's Hills - Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty

• Conquer Leith Hill - the highest peak of the area and second-highest in South-East England.

• See Leith Hill tower - an 18th century masterpiece and the highest point in South-East England

• Hike to Tilling Springs - where River Tillingbourne begins

• Discover the North Downs way and its stunning views towards Dorking

• Hike through England's largest vineyard - Denbies Wine Estate.

Photos - All photos were taken by the hike leader on previous trips so are the actual views that you will see from the route that you'll be hiking.

Transport & Meeting Point

We'll meet at Victoria station from 9:00am and leave the meeting point at 9:15am for the 9:25am train.

We'll meet close to Boots (no 27) Check on the map here of our meeting point:

Planned arrival time back into London of 6:30pm (we have a group train ticket and you are committed for the day until then).

Food

We will stop during the hike for a snack lunch so please bring food and drink. We will visit a pub after the hike where we can get refreshments.

Distance, Difficulty, Terrain and Elevation plot

Distance: 16.7km (10.4 miles)
Grading: Intermediate/Challenging
Rating: 6 out of 10
Ascent: 650m
Hiking time: About 5.5 to 6.5 hours of actual hiking

Cost

The trip is £18 per person which includes the guided hike and return train travel from the group departure station listed at the top of this event.

Price:
- Members: £14
- No Members: £18

IMPORTANT NOTE: To reserve a place you must make the full payment, otherwise the reservation will not be accepted.

Hiking in London

name: Saturday Morning Coffee: The Top 10 Guidelines for Better Composition
description:
This month's topic will be "How to Improve Your Photography with the Ten Commandments of Composition."
Composition is dependent on you and your ability to encompass what is necessary to produce an exciting photograph. No matter how you focus correctly, or expose correctly, if the image is uninteresting, it will be boring to the viewer. The old saying “Garbage in equals Garbage out” is the order of the day when it comes to proper, or pleasing compositions. All the expensive equipment you want to carry around can not fix a boring composition.

We must have at least 25 RSVP's or we will not be able to have this event. Using the projector requires that we have half the restaurant. This is not possible unless we have the minimum number of RSVP's.

A food or beverage purchase is not required. Please consider purchasing a beverage. They serve coffee, tea, Coke products and various juices. They are providing table service and will have a large room to cleanup after we leave.

The class is a more formal structure (unlike our Tuesday night classes) and Jeff will be using both a Keynote (PowerPoint) Presentation and a White Board to explain the basics of “How to Improve Your Photography with the Ten Commandments of Composition.”

The entire class is recorded, with audio, and will be available to download or stream for FREE for those that attend. Students will also be provided with a link to download all the slides used in the Keynote in PDF format. This will simplify note taking for some students.

If you do not attend the class or you miss a class, the recordings will be available to purchase or FREE for FCCP Supporter members.

What FCCP Members are saying about the class.

Jeff explains patiently, in a logical sequence, and with strict clarity. He continually checks for understanding, and dignifies all questions. His sense of humor puts everyone at ease . . . . . . Cade

Great class and great studio! I love learning in depth how a program works, so this class was spot on. I will be there next week! . . . . . . Kelly

Great group of people, great teacher & a comfortable, quiet meeting site! . . . Jane

I have had good instructors in the past, but Jeff Donald is by far the best. He speaks clearly and loudly, he knows his subject, he knows what is important to cover, he stays on task, he repeatedly asks for questions, he is friendly, he has a sense of humor, and he is everyone’s idea of a leader. . . . . . John

name: Art and Form Signature Series - Starla Lost
description:
Art and form Signature Series Photography Lighting Workshop.

We are happy to bring back one of our most popular signature series (started in 2011) again for you this April 25th!

What is the Art and Form series? - The workshop series is a fun and educational lighting workshop that is artfully lit and styled to give you outstanding images while teaching you lighting set ups designed to accentuate the human form and add drama to the poses. We will use accents pieces and accessories to style the shoot. This shoot does contain nudity.*

Who is our model for the evening? Starla Lost - our model for this workshop is an amazing professional art nude model from Ontario who is amazing at posing and is truly a joy to shoot with. She is personally one of my favourite models to work with and the images created are always awesome.

We are keeping this group small to only 6 photographers to give more time per person to shoot and for us to create some serious lighting set ups. We will be shooting in a studio equipped with a overhead pantograph system to allow us some serious speed and articulation/ manipulation of the lights.

Who/what is this workshop for? This workshop is suitable for all skill levels of photographer (we will give you the settings and tips) We will be doing 4 set ups throughout the evening and we will spend time discussing the set ups and the light modifiers we are using to shape the light.

Time is money, and we want everyone to get the most of their experience! That’s why we hold efficient classes; to allow for short, information packed sessions that maximize the shooting time for each participant. You can buy double shooting time in the workshop if you really want to get more time shooting a specify subject just email me for details if your interested in doubling your time in the workshop.

What we off from our workshops to our members

• A safe and comfortable, yet professional environment for everyone to gather, network, and of course, to take photos!

• An array of light modifiers such as; reflectors, umbrellas, soft-boxes, grids, snoots, and beauty dishes.

• Multiple, quick, one-on-one sessions with the model(s) to optimize your chances of getting that “perfect” shot- No turkey shoots!

“What should I bring to the session?!”

First thing’s first; you need your camera! Any model DSLR camera with a working hot-shoe is perfect! *Fresh batteries! (No one loves a dead battery, YIKES!)Formatted memory cards to ensure you can take as many lovely photos as possible!Your favourite lens; anything from 10mm-200mm will work just fine!Don’t forget to bring your passion for great photography and a thirst for knowledge!We will bring the fun! (WOO HOO!)

Who should take our sessions?

Our sessions are perfect for photographers who have a basic knowledge of their camera and its manual settings (don't worry -we will give you the F-stop and shutter speed for perfect results!). They are also suitable for any level of photographer looking to dive into different styles of photography, learn some great lighting set ups, and have some FUN!

name: FLASH FILL FUN
description: Your camera's flash isn't just for indoors. See how adding flash fill light to shadows on a sunny day can turn faces from the dark to light. Or if it's cloudy how direct flash exposure yields richer color. All levels of photographer are welcome but your camera must have a flash (built in or hot shoe) and at least a P mode setting. Barbie was booked so we've had to get another model. Free to meetup members and held weather permitting.

how_to_find_us: Nos vemos en el bar tomando un café
name: Clase de Fotografía: Laguna del Campillo
description:
Si te gusta la fotografía mientras disfrutas de un paseo sin prisas... Si quieres sacarle más partido a tu cámara de fotografiar y mejorar tu técnica fotográfica, sin importar cuál sea tu nivel. Si te apetece conocer gente, hacer amigos, pasar buenos momentos y descubrir nuevos paisajes... Sigue leyendo, esta actividad te puede interesar 😉

Os proponemos una clase de fotografía, que os servirá tanto de toma de contacto con la fotografía digital, como de refresco de conceptos ya olvidados.

En esta clase veremos los conceptos técnicos y ajustes necesarios para que aprendas a manejar tu cámara: Seleccionar los programas, controlar la exposición con la apertura de diafragma y la velocidad de obturación. Veremos y practicaremos cada uno de los conceptos, por lo que es necesario llevar la cámara.

Temario:
0 - Partes principales de la cámara
1 - La Exposición: Concepto y tipos
2 - Diafragma: Profundidad de Campo (PDC), Bokeh,
3 - La Velocidad de obturación: Concepto y situaciones de uso.
4 - La Sensibilidad: Concepto y situaciones de uso.
5 - Modos y tipos de enfoque
6 - Modos de funcionamiento: Manual, Automático y Semiautomático.
7 - Medición de la luz: Modos y situaciones de uso.
8 - Balance de blancos: Tipos

Al terminar la actividad tomaremos unas cañas/refrescos para descansar y charlar, antes de despedirnos 😉

Está actividad es gratuita.

• Equipo fotográfico recomendado
~ Cámara
~ Filtros: Polarizador y ND degradado
~ Tarjetas de memoria y baterías para la cámara

• Lo que hay que llevar
~ Calzado cómodo (deportivas o zapatillas de trekking)

how_to_find_us: Let's meet at the corner of Main and Moody Streets, right at the entrance to the Common
name: Watch City Steampunk Festival
description:
We've shot this festival on several occasions and it's one of my favorites. If you're unfamiliar with the Steampunk concept, a quick Google search will set you straight. In any event, these people are deep in their happy place, have amazing costumes which some of them have clearly spent LOTS of time and money on and are dying for someone to come up and ask if you can take their picture.

This bills itself as the largest outdoor Steampunk Festival in the US and has been going on since 2010. Website here: https://www.watchcityfestival.com/
If the weather is halfway decent, the turnout is usually very high and I guaranty you'll come away with some treasured photographs. Starts at 10:00 and that's when I've set the meetup for but there will be many more people later that morning and afternoon so don't worry about showing up late.

GEAR: This is mostly a portrait opportunity so bring a fast lens or two (f/2.8 or faster would be ideal but, as always, bring what ya got and make it work) to get that good subject separation. I also strongly suggest an off camera speed light to tame full sun shadows or emphasize subjects in the shade.

PARKING: Public lot about a block away at Central Square Parking between Common & Lexington streets. Also 3 minute walk from commuter rail stop.

name: FYI -Steampunk Festival , Waltham MA. May 11th , 2019
description:
Hello Again, this event was brought to me by one of our members. Check it out online to see if you are interested in a Photo-Op. If several people RSVP , I will change it to a field trip and set-up a carpooling . Also, look at the websites & youtube.

Hello! Thanks for your interest in our festival. It is a free one-day event on Saturday May 11th, 10am to 5pm, and will be held rain or shine. Much of the event is held in public on Waltham Common in downtown Waltham, MA. You are free to take photos, although if you are getting up close to someone please do ask their permission and give them a chance to pose (most people will be happy to do so).

Steampunk is a mix of the Victorian era, science fiction, and whimsy, as if the world that H.G. Wells and Jules Verne imagined came true. Here is a video I did earlier this year in an attempt to explain it: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kg6zqjE27II

Our event involves music, performers, children's events, vendors, and this year in particular a "Mad Science Expo" which should offer some wacky contraptions to photograph. You can find photos and videos from previous years in the "Galleries" section of our website, https://www.watchcityfestival.com/.
If your group would be interested in additional photo opportunities in Waltham, I can recommend the nearby Charles River Museum of Industry and Innovation ( https://www.charlesrivermuseum.org/).

We hope to see you there!

Melissa Honig
Lead Organizer
Watch City Steampunk Festival
A project of the Downtown Waltham Partnership
We're on Facebook, Twitter, and Instagram!

The trail is primarily used for hiking, walking, nature trips, and birding and is accessible year-round. Dogs are also able to use this trail but must be kept on leash.

name: Whole Earth Festival Davis
description:
The yearly Whole Earth Festival on the UC Davis campus quad is a wonderful explosion of colorful garb, colorful people (visualize Humboldt hippies), colorful booths with excellent juried crafts for sale, great music, and healthy food. Starting as a small class event in 1969, it has grown into a large festival honoring art, music, and environmental concerns. Lots of photo ops, as you can imagine.
There's a parking structure on Howard Way off Russell Blvd. (unfortunately $9, so you may want to try to find a parking place on a nearby street), with a bus stop/lawn area roughly in front of the parking structure. Let's meet at the bus stop area (I'll have a sign) at 10 am, and go exploring! (Ignore the red pin, which won't move to the right place.) You're welcome to stay as late as you want to, as the music and festivities continue into the evening...actually, for the whole weekend!

name: Spend the day on the frieghter Col. James M. Schoonmaker
venue_name: National Museum of the Great Lakes
description:
You must register using the following link to insure your spot on at this event. Premium Members save $5.00
http://cvpw.link/frieghter

Join us as we explore and photograph on of the grand lake freighter of the past. We will have access to many areas of the Col. James M. Schoonmaker. this ship is docked in Toledo Oh and is part of the National Great Lakes Museum . From the wheel house the the engine space, there are many great photo ops on this ship.
Instruction in various techniques will be presented. Using fill flash and interior panorama shots, plus more.
Admission to the National Museum of the Great Lakes and the Freighter is not included in the event fee. Museum and Ship admission is $15.00 ( Discount for seniors, AAA and Military )
After our time on the ship , we can head over to Tony Packo's for the Hungarian hot dogs made famous by Max Klinger on Tv's MASH.

This is not a dedicated tour. The ship will be open to other touring the ship. I have scheduled this early in there season to avoid summer or school crowds.
Due to its historical accuracy, the Col. James M .Schoonmaker Museum Ship is not handicap accessible. Narrow, steep staircases are common throughout the Schoonmaker and may provide difficulties in accessibility for some.

Col. James M. Schoonmaker

The Col. James M. Schoonmaker was built at the Great Lakes Engineering Works of Ecorse, Michigan. She was christened by Gretchen Schoonmaker daughter of the ship’s namesake and launched on July 1, 1911. The Schoonmaker was unsurpassed in both size and elegance. On her maiden trip, she carried 12,650 net tons of coal from Toledo, Ohio to Sheboygan, Wisconsin. The ship held the title of “Queen of the Lakes” as the largest ship operating on the Great Lakes until April 14, 1914.

You must register using the following link to insure your spot on at this event.
http://cvpw.link/frieghter

name: Introduction to Lightroom for New Photographers
description:
Looking for a simple solution to manage all the photographs you have stored on your camera? Want to take those ho-hum photos and bring them to life with just a few quick clicks? .. Lightroom is an application for importing, managing, editing and sharing your digital photographs.

The biggest selling feature of Lightroom is that it is a "Non Destructive" editing software.. So no matter what you do to your photographs in Lightroom, your original file never gets touched. You can always get your files back to their original state.

This introductory course will show you how to import your photos into Lightroom, manage your folders, and teach you the fundamentals of editing your photos to look amazing!

Attendees can upload the software onto their computers for free by visiting..

https://www.adobe.com/ca/products/photoshop-lightroom/free-trial-download.html

Bring your computer to the class and start learning right away!
Students are encouraged to arrive 5-10 minutes early to get acquainted and pay their fees.

Class sizes are kept to only 10 students for easy and effective learning.

Requirements:
Laptop with Adobe Lightroom software pre-installed
5 or more of your favourite photos to edit
Portable storage drive (if you have one but not mandatory) .

Instructor recommends you import your photos to your computer before you come to the class. But if you can't and if you still have your photographs on your camera's memory card, you must bring the appropriate memory card reader, or your entire camera with the USB cable to transfer the files.

Who is the meetup for:

• New Photographers
• Photographers new to Lightroom.
• Lightroom users looking to create an organized, easy to manage photo
library.

how_to_find_us: We're in the glass door next to HMV
name: Time to Write - Worcester
description:
When do you get time to write?

If you write professionally or for fun co-working could be a great opportunity to get time, space and accountability to meet your goals and get those words on the page.

Time to Write is a new co-working group for writers in Worcester. We will be meeting at the Kiln 0.5 on Saturday 11th May from 10am to 4pm.

The idea is simple, we meet at the beginning of the day for some quick introductions and goal setting, after that it’s 5 hours of quiet working with no distractions. We’ll take a couple of coffee or lunch breaks along the way. At 3.15 you can go home in the knowledge that you’ve done the most writing you’ve got done all month, OR you can stick around for 45 minutes of discussion about an element of writing, news about local writing opportunities and networking with other writers.

Our first session is FREE – which is an excellent opportunity to take advantage of the inspiring setting of The Kiln 0.5 at no cost. In the future we will be charging a small fee towards venue and refreshment costs, but we want to make it affordable and inclusive for everyone, so come to our first meeting where our discussion point will be all about how our co-working group will run, how much future sessions will cost and what we want it to be.

What do you need to do for the first session?
* Sign up on Meetup
* Bring something to write with – your weapon of choice, laptop, notebook, pens. If you have a file with your current project saved on it don’t forget that too
* Remember your headphones – we will be working in silence, so if you like to write to music, these will be essential
* Bring a contribution towards the coffee machine (the Kiln are very kindly letting us use theirs) and any lunch/snacks you need – at the moment refreshments aren’t provided, although you never know, there may be some homemade, vegan cake

name: Portrait practice session
description:
Let's practice taking portaits together among fellow photographers!

We will visit a number of different locations in and around "Schloss Blutenburg" with diverse backgrounds and lighting conditions, and learn from each other regarding framing, lighting, posing, and directing.

After a short introduction we will split into small groups, and everyone will take turn to be each other's model. Don't worry, we are all shy photographers to begin with––more happy to be behind the camera than in front of it. But because we know we are in it together to improve our skills, and everyone will go through the same process, these sessions almost always turn out to be filled with laugther and fun! And beside getting more experienced in taking portraits, you will get some new facebook profile pics of yourself as well :)

The focus is on natural lighting, but if you have reflectors or flashes, you are welcome to bring them along and experiment with them also!

This is an outdoor event, so in case the weather forecast is bad (heavy rain) on this particular day, we will cancel the event. So please check this event around Friday noon.

name: Explore Toronto Downtown Core – Walking Tour
description:
Join us for a tour in Downtown Toronto! We will visit Nathan Philip Square, City Hall, Financial District, Union Station and St Lawrence Market. This is a great way of visiting some of Toronto’s iconic places. We will show you around as a local.

We will meet in front of the Chelsea Hotel, and we will start our tour by walking on Bay St. We will see some interesting places along the way, but our first stop is going to be at Nathan Philip Square. This place is my favourite in the city since you can take the famous Toronto selfie.

Our next stop will be the Financial District. We will observe the architecture of Canada’s biggest banks and we will check some other places that are in the area like Brookfield Place. We will take a break (and pictures) and we will go to our next stop.

We will walk to Union Station which is next to the Financial District in order to check the architecture of the old building (and take more pictures). We will discuss some of the places you can go using the station and we will go to our final stop.

Our last stop is going to be St Lawrence Market. Grab a bite or walk around the famous Toronto market were you can find a variety of Canadian and international food. After the tour is over feel free to stay and chat with other members of the meetup!

THIS TOUR INCLUDES:
• Bay Street
• Nathan Philip Square
• Financial District
• The PATH
• Union Station
• St Lawrence Market

WHEN AND WHERE TO MEET?
10:00 am – Chelsea Hotel (Meeting in front of the lobby at 33 Gerrard St W)

COST:
$5 per person, and the payment can be done at the meeting point before we start the tour.

WHAT TO BRING?
Comfortable clothes, water, and camera

CONTACT INFO:
- Cell phone[masked]
- or Meetup message

DISCLAIMER:
In the tours sometimes pictures are taken by the organizers or other members. Therefore, by attending the tour you automatically consent to these pictures being taken & used as they see fit. If you don’t want to appear in any picture please let the organizer know before the beginning of the event.

P.S. Vi ricordiamo che GitUp non è un’ agenzia viaggi ma un’associazione no profit che cerca di aggregare persone per passare momenti di piacevole condivisione.

name: Basic Photo Editing: Lightroom
description:
Before you can attend this Meetup, you must first pay and register here. (http://www.precision-camera.com/lightroom-101)

Managing and editing your images as a new photographer can be daunting. How do you import your images? What basic editing should you do? How do you share the results with the world?

This class will jump start your image editing pipeline using Adobe Lightroom Classic CC. We will discuss the basics of workflow (something every photographer needs just a little of), and then jump into basic editing in Lightroom Classic CC including white balance, exposure, levels, and curves.

Students should bring their laptop and will be provided a set of images so they can “click along” with the instructor. Students are also welcome to work on their own images.

Concepts Covered
How to import your images.
Where to store your images.
Basic image editing: white balance, exposure, levels & curve.
Cropping and rotating images.
Dust and spot removal.
Exporting your images to share or print.
Already comfortable with this? Check out our Intermediate Photo Editing: Lightroom class that covers more advanced editing such as local adjustments, detailed color editing, and other advanced features.

Audience
This class is perfect for anyone that loves to take photographs from beginner to longtime photographer. Adobe Lightroom is great at helping you organize your digital images so you can find them, share and enjoy them. There are many advantages to Adobe Lightroom over Photoshop. If you want to learn photo software I would suggest starting with Adobe Lightroom.

Required Equipment
A computer with Adobe Lightroom Classic CC installed and working.
A note pad and pen to take notes if you would like to or a tablet or computer for taking notes.
You may bring a laptop if you want to follow along with your own images; however, the instructor will not be able to provide computer, OS or application support.

Schedule and Format
This is a very hands-on class lasting 3 hours with a break around the halfway point.

About the Instructor
Scott is a photographer based out of Cedar Park, Texas. He has a studio in his home and runs Scott D Photography with his wife, Jennifer. Scott fell in love with photography about 10 years ago while working in Chicago and began the long journey of learning all he could. His favorite subject continues to be the concept of "urban decay" and his business focuses on family and children portraiture.

Scott loves two things about photography. First, you can never learn it all. Second, the industry is brimming with other professionals willing and enthusiastic about guiding you through your next photographic adventure. Teaching has always been a passion for Scott, and he's thrilled to continue that passion.

how_to_find_us: We'll meet just OUTSIDE of Exit C1
name: Visit Lady Yang's / 楊氏 Grave  (Dr. Sun Yat-sen's Mum)
description:
The idea that Dr. Sun Yat-sen, co-founder of modern China, buried his beloved Mother (and fellow revolutionary) here in Hong Kong is interesting in and of itself. Add in the fact that his hometown is over 75 kilometers away in Zhongshan / 中山, Guangdong makes it all the more intriguing.

Also interesting is Dr. Sun's unique relationship with women. His many marriages (sometimes running concurrently!) and other histoire de coeur are legendary. He seems to have been every bit the charismatic revolutionary that we see in all the photographs. What is less well know, however, is his relationship with his own mother especially during his formative years before and after he set off to Hawai'i as a young boy.

There is scant biographical information about Lady Yang but I think it is still worthwhile to try and fill in the gaps given the vaulted place the Sun family occupies. It is also important, I think, to remember Lady Yang not just as Dr. Sun's Mother but as an important figure in her own right.

This event will be a great way to explore the many layers of Hong Kong history from dynastic to modern. The first leg of the route is considered "Easy" by hiking enthusiasts BUT keep in mind it is uphill along Fei Ngo Shan Road - 飛鵞山道. We'll return by walking down a portion of Wilson Trail, Section 4. This part of the Wilson Trail is more advanced with slick rocks and more jungle-like conditions so the right footwear is a must. The benefit will be that we'll walk along a local "ancient trail" and past the semi-abandoned village, Wong Keng Tsai 黃麖仔 on our way back to Clearwater Bay Road. Great for photos of both nature and ruin-like structures.

Those of you who'd like to avoid the last part of the adventure, no need to worry as I'll organize a group to return by walking down FNS Road.

name: Special Autumn Event - Breenhold Gardens, Mt Wilson
description: ABOUT-The heritage listed Garden Estate of Breenhold at Mount Wilson is one of the most extensive privately owned garden properties in Australia. FOCUS OF THE SHOOT-The focus for this shoot will be “Contrast Colours” and to continue to expand on discussions about focal point, exposure and composition. We ask that you stay within the bounds of Breenhold Gardens. The event will start and end inside the Gardens. There are many wonderful places in the gardens to feed your imagination: trees showcasing stunning autumn leaves and leaf carpeted undergrowth, hidden gardens, statues and old rock steps. Members may shoot on their own or in groups or may spend time with the coordinators. It is completely up to you. If you are not familiar with the area the coordinators will be more than happy to brief you on some ideas. SHOOT DURATION–10:00am to 1:00pm - This includes a 15 min introduction to the coordinators, each member and the plan for the shoot. MEETING PLACE-The coordinators are meeting outside the entry gate to the gardens at 9:30am to enjoy a cuppa before the event. You are most welcome to join us (please remember to bring your thermos and or your morning tea). The shoot will start at 10:00am, we will be waiting outside the entry gates to the gardens and will be easy to spot. Just look for 2 women with camera gear, and smiles awaiting other fabulous women! Please be on time so you don’t miss the introductions. COSTS-$17.50 in total. Entry Fee to Gardens-$12.50 payable at the main gates on entry. EFTPOS is available. Meetup Event Fee-$5:00 to be paid to the Meetup coordinator at the beginning of the Event. Please pay in cash and please bring the exact amount. Please note we do not have Credit Card or EFTPOS facilities. Please also note there are no discounts or transfer of fees to another Event. LUNCH AFTER THE EVENT-The are no cafes at Mt Wilson and it is such a beautiful location we thought it would be fun to share a picnic in the gardens. If you would like to join us please bring a picnic lunch and a picnic blanket; they can be left in your car during the event. Please note that coming to the picnic afterwards is not mandatory, it is just a good chance to sit and chat about the shoot and get to know each other. IF IT RAINS–Mountain weather can be unpredictable. If rain is intermittent we will continue, however if it is set in we will cancel the shoot and all members will be sent a message, via MeetUp by 6am on the morning of the event. EQUIPMENT SUGGESTIONS–This is a day time shoot so hand held cameras will cope brilliantly. Camera/s, lenses (wide/prime/zoom), tripod if you wish. Remember to ensure your camera battery is fully charged and that you have a spare. As this is Autumn also bring something to protect your gear from any rain or fog. A NOTE ABOUT GEAR – The coordinators do not provide any photography equipment/gear of any type, at anytime for group or individual member use. Please ensure you bring everything you need. WHAT TO WEAR–Comfortable, warm, waterproof shoes, warm clothing. Sunburn cream is always a wise accessory. Water to ensure you stay hydrated and an umbrella / wet weather clothing as the weather changes rapidly in the mountains. HOW TO GET THERE Car–is the only transport option. 29 The Avenue, Mount Wilson, NSW. DISCLAIMER - By indicating your planned attendance at our Event you understand you will attend at your own risk. Our intent is to take all care in the organisation and execution of the event however we are simply facilitating the opportunity of like-minded women to socialise and enjoy photography, and maybe learn some new skills, while also making new friends. No responsibility will be taken, by the co coordinators, for any loss or damage of any equipment or injury of any kind to your person before, during or after the Event. Any photos taken that contain any other group member may not be posted to any form of social media without the express permission or invitation of the said member.

name: Steam Train, Secret Nuclear Bunker & Essex Way – Long Country Hike
description:
Walk length 14.5miles/23km approx. Circular.

A substantial & quirky hike following a large section of the Essex Way long distance footpath through ancient woodland & open farmland from a visit to a former Cold War Bunker/Civil Defence Centre at Kelvedon Hatch.

The first part of the hike is 4miles approx from Chipping Ongar to Kelvedon Hatch and the former nuclear bunker where we will have a long lunch to give us time to visit (approx 1.5hrs).

Kelvedon Hatch was set up initially as an RAF ROTOR Station (1950's air defence radar to detect soviet bombers) then developed into a Regional Government HQ designed to shelter up to 600 government and military staff in the advent of a nuclear war; it is the largest and deepest of its kind open to the public in South East England. Decommissioned in 1992 & converted into a private museum.

Lunch & Finish: Bring water & snack lunch. This walk should finish at about 6.30pm, however the time may be slightly earlier or later than this depending on the weather and pace (depending on time needed to see the bunker). This is a complete day event and you are advised not to plan evening arrangements. You can visit the canteen at the Bunker (the Bunker canteen uses only cash and can be slow).

We will have a pub stop at the end of the walk near Epping Underground Station.

The Epping Ongar heritage railway was the final section of the Great Eastern Railway branch line & later part of the London Underground closing in 1994, since 2012 it has been a heritage steam railway.

PLEASE NOTE THIS IS A GENTLY UNDULATING HIKE BUT ALSO LONG AND WILL BE WALKED AT A BRISK PACE SO WE HAVE TIME TO VISIT THE BUNKER AND GET BACK. PLEASE DO NOT SIGN UP FOR THIS WALK IF YOU ARE NOT HAPPY WITH THIS.

Meeting/Transport & cost (PLEASE READ!)

Meet outside Epping underground station at 10.00am to catch the 339 Heritage Bus at 10.25am that gets to North Weald for 10.37am. The heritage train service is at 11am from North Weald and arrives at Ongar for 11.15am for the hike to start.

There is a normal bus service the 420 that leaves from the station at 10.50am and gets to Ongar for 11.15am (this may be an option if spaces sell out for the heritage bus service). By doing this you could still do the hike and bunker visit.

Epping station is on zone 6. The car park is around £2.50, other free off road street parking may be available (please check for restrictions and leave enough time to park).

Cost for the day will be about £27

Meetup/walk guide cost is £6 cash on the day.

Museum Cost
The cost to visit the bunker is £7.50 or £7 which is the group discount price (we need at least 15 to get the group discount). This is self guided with a handset. You will need cash for this.
See Kelvedon Hatch (www.secretnuclearbunker.com/index.html).

Heritage Railway
Ticket for an adult is £14 cash which includes a mixture of heritage bus and railway which should be a steam train but may vary on the day.
I CAN OBTAIN ADVANCED TICKETS FOR THE HERITAGE TRAIN SERVICE FOR THE DAY, THIS WOULD ENSURE A SPOT (MESSAGE ME IF YOU ARE INTERESTED AS I WOULD NEED PAYMENT IN ADVANCE).

Please make a note of the organizers numbers - Colin[masked].

RSVP: The organizers monitor non-attendance; please update your RSVP beforehand. Please see our RSVP policy (http://www.meetup.com/London-Explorers/pages/RSVP_for_Walks/)

Weather: See also BBC Weather (http://www.bbc.co.uk/weather/)
Please see our weather policy

Walking Safety: Walking is a great way to keep fit and generally very safe; however it does contain an element of risk. Before going on any of these walks you need to be reasonably fit and be prepared to be responsible for your own safety. You should wear appropriate clothing such as proper walking boots, warm and wet weather clothing and carry sufficient food and water. Please see our Terms and Conditions (http://www.meetup.com/London-Explorers/pages/Terms_and_Conditions/)

name: The Berkeley Rose Garden & Cragmont Rock Park Walk
group_name: Walking in San Francisco for Health and History
description:
Now open for RSVPs. The only cost is $3 cash for adults. At 11:00 AM we will meet in front of "Passione Caffe" which used to be "PIQ Berkeley." I just today found out that "PIQ Berkeley" went out of business last November. It was our gathering point for this walk for years.

It is close to the Berkeley Downtown BART Station and hopefully it will be just like it was before: a good cafe, bakery, & pizza place. I will try to sit or stand outside.

We will eat our sack lunches at the Berkeley Rose Garden so people should either bring a lunch or buy one at our starting point or one of the many other cafes and sandwich places nearby. I advise bringing water & paper towels.

We expect to start walking at 11:15 AM. We will walk to areas around and also North of the Rose Garden hard uphill all the way to our furthest North and highest spot, Cragmont Rock Park. Then it is easy returning, all downhill. We will walk several stairways and passageways. We will visit the Berkeley Art Center near Live Oak Park. I estimate the distance at 5 miles & our return to our starting point at 4:30 PM.

Link to Passione Caffe: http://passionebrands.com/passione-caffe/

Below is a link to a site about the Berkeley Rose Garden:

http://www.berkeleyheritage.com/berkeley_landmarks/municipal-rose-garden.html

Some legal disclaimers: By joining us for any event you hereby RELEASE and DISCHARGE it's organizers, hosts and participants from any and all liability, claims, demands or causes of action that you now have, or may have in the future, for injuries, damages, death and/or economic loss of any kind or nature, arising in whole or in part out of the activities, advice or information contained herein. You further agree that if you or someone under your supervision uses the information on this website you assume all risks of injury, damage, and economic loss, without limitation, and release providers from all liability therefore. It is advisable to consult a doctor before you begin any strenuous physical activity. The organizer is not trained for emergency medical procedures and no doctors, nurses or ambulances are provided on the walks.

Photos above show what we will see on this walk in the right order.

We have a starting point (above) previously called PIQ Berkeley, but is now Passione Caffe.

Above is a closer view of PIQ Berkeley (Passione Caffe).

Walking through the religious schools.

A double staircase before we reach the Berkeley Rose Garden.

A wedding in progress with live music at the rose garden.

A wedding in progress with live music at the rose garden.

Some flowers at the rose garden [masked]).

Flowers after rose garden, but before we reached Cragmont Rock.

name: Free fun event for all, Art of the Automobile in the Copley Square Plaza!
description:
I LOVE Boston! I've lived here since 1959 and grown with our city as we offer more and more fantastic free public events. And spectating is free at the Art of the Automobile in Boston's Copley Square Plaza, a unique event where the owners of special exotic, expensive and historic cars proudly display their treasured vehicles as they also support the Martin Richard Foundation.

I have attended this event since its inception, that's my photo above from 2016. Everyone is welcome and the owners are happy to talk with you, so you don't need to be a car genius!

https://www.facebook.com/ArtoftheAutomobileBoston/posts/832628047102778

"This spring's event benefactor, the Martin Richard Foundation (TeamMR8.org), allows our Automotive community to 'foster greater togetherness, compassion, peace and kindness in our communities through activities that build bridges and bring people together'. In particular, the funds raised by this event, will go to organizing programming at Martin's Park at the Smith Family Waterfront next to the Boston Children's Museum.

Whether displaying a vehicle or coming to spectate, we look forward to celebrating all that is octane related on May 11th with you."

https://www.eventbrite.com/e/art-of-the-automobile-2019-spring-expo-tickets-58391867648

On April 15, 2013, two bombs exploded near the Boston Marathon Finish Line. Martin Richard was one of three people killed while the Richard Family and hundreds of others were injured. When a photo of Martin holding a handmade sign that read 'No More Hurting People, Peace' was shared over the Internet, his message created a feeling of unity, kindness and peace. These values have become the pillars of the Martin Richard Foundation which was founded in January 2014.

name: Heart of the Park: Central Park Photo Workshop
venue_address_1: Central Park West and W. 72nd Street
venue_name: CENTRAL PARK WEST ENTRANCE AT 72ND STREET
description:
**** NOTE! BEFORE your RSVP to this Workshop, please go to Please go to http://www.cityscape-photo.com/workshops/2019/05/11/nyc-heart-of-the-park-central-park to register and pay ****

Saturday in the Park! What could be better…except a Photo Workshop with popular photo tour leader and Central Park maven Steve Rosenbach!

Back by popular demand... several members wanted to come to the last one but couldn't make that date.

This is a photo workshop that I carefully designed so as to get the maximum amount of great photo opportunities within about a 3 hour easy walk. I’m limiting the number of people who can attend, so that I can spend time with each of you to help with anything you need in getting really compelling images of the sites that we visit along the way. That can range from basic photo or camera help to assistance with composition and advanced techniques.

Also, as an added value, you'll be able to send me your photos (or links to them) from this workshop for evaluation and feedback. I'll make comments and suggestions, and in many cases, do some photo editing on your photos to demonstrate how to make a good image even better.

Our first stop will be Strawberry Fields, an intimate haven just inside the park set aside as a memorial to John Lennon. From there, we’ll circumnavigate The Lake to take advantage of panoramic views with the elegant skylines of Central Park West or Fifth Avenue in the background.

We’ll “get lost” in The Ramble, a bucolic, forested tract with a picturesque stream and rustic bridges where, for the moment, you can imagine that the city is far away.

Finally, we’ll arrive at Bethesda Terrace, an iconic, romantic plaza that you’ll recognize from countless movies. We’ll explore the Terrace from the grand sweep of its monumental staircases to the intricate carvings of honeybees and birds along its steps.

All together, we'll see 30 unique and photogenic features in the heart of Central Park, and along the way, Steve will regale you with stories of the Park and the specific sites we'll visit.

It will be a journey that will delight your sense of color, texture, and proportion as well as refresh your spirit.

**** NOTE! BEFORE your RSVP to this Workshop, please go to Please go to http://www.cityscape-photo.com/workshops/2019/05/11/nyc-heart-of-the-park-central-park to register and pay ****

REGISTER NOW FOR THE SPECIAL EARLY BIRD PRICE at http://www.cityscape-photo.com/workshops/2019/05/11/nyc-heart-of-the-park-central-park

BONUS!
All participants will receive a gift card worth $25 towards prints and other photo products at Nations Photo Lab https://www.nationsphotolab.com/

name: Street Photography Class
description:
This 3 hour class is presented by the Calgary Amateur Photographers Group. If you're shy about pointing your camera at people, but would love to learn how to do some street photography, then this is a great opportunity!

In this class you'll learn the tips and tricks for getting great shots and some useful camera settings. We will also talk about how to overcome the fear or discomfort of taking photos of people. You will also learn how to look for the interesting shots.

The class will involve discussion and practice as we wander around the area of Stephen Avenue area of downtown.

What to bring:

While you can bring any type of camera to this class, the content will focus on modern digital cameras. As far as lense, the best for this class would be in the 17-40mm range, but you can bring any lens.
Make sure to have a fully charged battery and room on your memory card.

Skill level:

This class is suitable for beginner photographers, however the focus of the class will not be on how to use your camera. I will suggest and talk about settings to use. If you are not sure about how to set your camera, I will try to help, but bring your camera manual in case you need to refer to it.

The instructor of this class will be me (David Watson), you can find some of my street photography shots at CalgaryGuy1 onInstagram

See you there!

name: Taller: Fotografía de Paisaje y larga exposición diurna
description:
Si te gusta la naturaleza, el paisajismo, la fotografía panorámica y la fotografía de alta calidad (HDR) este taller es para ti.

Tendremos una sesión teórica y práctica de 3 horas, donde se verá desde la preparación de una sesión de fotos, la configuración de la cámara, técnicas, herramientas, accesorios útiles y el uso de los filtros de densidad neutra y degradados, para este tipo de fotografía.

¿Qué desarrollaremos en este taller?

• Configuración de la cámara para paisajes
• Transición desde Modo Asistido a modo Manual completo.
• Resaltando efectos dramáticos en configuración Manual.
• Fotografía panorámica. Trípode y cabezales idóneos para este tipo de fotografía y como evitar "la paralaje"
• Uso del Bracketing u horquillado (para HDR)
• Uso de filtros.
• Fotos de larga exposición diurna.

¿Dónde lo realizaremos?
He elegido como lugar una de las cascadas más altas de la Comunidad de Madrid, la Chorrera de los Litueros, ya que tiene mucho espacio muy foto-génico para el paisajismo y la naturaleza, por lo que será una estupenda excursión fotográfica haciendo incluso algo de senderismo por los alrededores.

El equipo con el que deberás contar:
• Cámara (con función manual)
• Trípode
• Filtro de densidad neutra (ND Grad. Densidad Neutra Graduado).
• Opcional: Disparador con cable o remoto.
• Ropa y calzado cómodo para andar por el campo, agua y snacks para mantener la energía.

Sino no tienes los filtros no hay problema, de todas formas tengo unos filtros universales que podemos compartir entre todos, así los pruebas y más adelante decides cuales comprarte. También llevaré mi cámara y el trípode para dejárselo a los que no cuenten el equipo necesario (pero tendréis que compartirlo entre todos). Intentad, eso si, traer vuestra propia tarjeta de memoria SD para guardar vuestras imágenes.

Al terminar la sesión, los que podáis nos quedaremos por la zona para picar o comer algo para socializar y compartir la experiencia.

Nota: Al apuntarte el sistema te preguntará por tu correo electrónico para ponerme en contacto contigo, darte el punto de encuentro exacto, coordinar la forma de pago y enviarte las diapositivas del taller para que las imprimas o las cargues en tu tableta o dispositivo móvil y se te haga más fácil tomar apuntes en la sesión.

El desplazamiento se hará en vehículos propios, si alguien desea comparitr coche (gastos compartidos entre los pasajeros) que lo comente aquí vismo y nos vamos organizando.

Coste del Taller: 30€.

name: (FEATURING Starla Lost)Intro to fashion Lighting techniques- $29.95
description:
Join us in studio for a Lighting lesson!

We have a new series of lighting skill based educational lighting workshops with a true emphasis on learning lighting skills.If you are looking to improve your Fashion lighting skills and delve into the world of Fashion Photography this is the workshop for you!

We have a wonderful and talented model Starla - coming in to model for our lighting class as a special treat!

We will discuss the fundamental elements of a fashion shoot, how to pick modifiers based on the designers wishes for the clothing. We will learn to ultilize modifiers to accentuate the fabrics and create stunning beautiful lighting in studio.

We will have learning tools including designer outfits, a model for the shoot and a printed hand out for you to take home.
We are limiting the class size to only 6 participants for this lesson

Who/what is this workshop for? This workshop is suitable for all skill levels of photographer (we will give you the settings for proper exposure and tips for shooting)

Time is money, and we want everyone to get the most of their experience! That’s why we hold efficient classes; to allow for short, information packed sessions that maximize the shooting/learning time for each participant. You can buy double shooting time in the workshop if you really want to get more time shooting a specify subject just email me for details if your interested in doubling your time in the workshop.

What we off from our workshops to our members

• A safe and comfortable, yet professional environment for everyone to gather, network, and of course, to take photos!

• An array of light modifiers such as; reflectors, umbrellas, soft-boxes, grids, snoots, and beauty dishes.

“What should I bring to the session?!”

First thing’s first; you need your camera! Any model DSLR camera with a working hot-shoe is perfect! *Fresh batteries! (No one loves a dead battery, YIKES!)Formatted memory cards to ensure you can take as many lovely photos as possible!Your favourite lens; anything from 10mm-200mm will work just fine!Don’t forget to bring your passion for great photography and a thirst for knowledge!We will bring the fun! (WOO HOO!)

Who should take our sessions?

Our sessions are perfect for photographers who have a basic knowledge of their camera and its manual settings (don't worry -we will give you the F-stop and shutter speed for perfect results!). They are also suitable for any level of photographer looking to dive into different styles of photography, learn some great lighting set ups, and have some FUN!

how_to_find_us: Meet outside the Lodge Coffee House
name: Tree ID
description:
This will be a collective effort to improve our tree identification skills - each of us knows something, however little, and together I'm sure we know a lot! Or at least can figure it out.

So bring your tree ID books and guides, and we'll stroll along the path see what we can identify from the bark, leaves, buds, catkins, and overall shape of the tree.

If folk fancy it, and it's not too busy, we could have a drink & snack in the Lodge Coffee House after.

Remember to bring £ donation for Meetup admin costs.

description:
~~ Disco Dance Party~~~

Check out their website - http://www.lagunadelsol.com/ - and/or give them a call for more info -[masked]. They have a 2-for-1 admission coupon on the website that you may be able to use - http://www.lagunadelsol.com/first-timer-coupon/
~~~~~~~~~~~~
Laguna del Sol is one of the premier clothing-optional resorts in the United States. Located on 250 acres near Sacramento, it’s close to the city and yet a world away. Everyone’s idea of the perfect, relaxing getaway is different. Laguna del Sol aims to provide a full range of active and leisure activities to be enjoyed with the luxury of not having to dress. Deluxe, modern facilities blend smoothly into the lush, green lawns that cover much of the grounds. Nudity feels incredibly natural in this beautiful environment.

Questions, Private message me...
thanks~
Brad

NOTE: First Time guests need to arrive between 10 am and no later than 2:45 pm so you can ride along for the free 15 minute orientation tour.

how_to_find_us: Delante del N 16 del Paseo de Recoletos
name: PIRATAS, ESPIONAJE NAVAL, BARCOS PIRATA, INVENTOS Y MANUSCRITOS DE DA VINCI...
description:
Esta mañana de sábado aprenderás y te divertiras con un juego donde tendràs que resolver una serie de preguntas sobre temas tan apasionantes como la piratería, sus embarcaciones, el espionaje naval, inventos de DaVinci....

Esta caza del tesoro se llevará a cabo en pequeños grupos, a cada uno de los cuales se os dará una serie de preguntas basadas en PISTAS QUE ENCONTRARÉIS OBSERVANDO LOS INVENTOS Y LOS MANUSCRITOS DE DAVINCI Y A TRAVÉS DE LA CONTEMPLACIÓN DE LAS RUTAS MARÍTIMAS, BARCOS PIRATA Y ACCIONES DE ESPIONAJE ENTRE ASIA Y ESPAÑA, desplegadas en una interesante exposición.

PRECIO. 6 EUROS, 5 si se abonan con antelación en la web: www.planbclub.es

A la hora de resolver esta caza del tesoro seremos TESTIGOS DE MANUSCRITOS DE LEONARDO DA VINCI, donde el artista dejó huella de algunos de los temas que llegó a dominar como la ingeniería, la mecánica y el arte. PODREMOS VER RECONSTRUCCIONES DE MÁQUINAS DE ESOS MANUSCRITOS, ASÍ COMO UNO DE SUS MAYORES PROYECTOS: el enorme caballo diseñado para Ludovico Sforza.

El trabajo en grupo a la hora de localizar las diferentes respuestas es la clave de este encuentro.

Una vez hayáis contestado a las preguntas tomaremos algo, mientras determinamos quién es el grupo ganador del cual, dos de sus componentes, podrán acudir a una actividad de planb gratis.

name: Novice Photography Bootcamp
description:
This is a paid workshop, please don't RSVP until you have registered at https://lorenphotos.com/mevents/novice-photography-bootcamp/

There are some essential skills that you must master before you will get consistently good photographs every time you go out to shoot. In this workshop, you will create a strong foundation from which you’ll be able to get the shots you want and you'll enjoy making pictures even more. You will understand all the elements of your camera, what you can control on your camera, which settings you should use and which ones are just there creating confusion.

You have the option of attending in person or live online. The five hour workshop is structured so you don’t get overwhelmed with too much info at once. You’ll be given fun, easy exercises to do during the day that will help you practice what we talk about. We’ll take it one step at a time and make sure you understand what you are doing before moving on. You'll receive handouts that you can use when you are out making pictures.

Some topics we’ll cover:

• How to set up your camera (yes, there specific settings you want to change to make your camera perform better)
• Photography terminology
• Properly holding the camera
• The exposure triangle: ISO, shutter speed and aperture
• Understanding the light meter settings
• File size settings
• Wide angle, normal and telephoto lenses
• How to focus and which focus setting to use
• Basics of composition

This is a fun, light-hearted seminar filled with personal attention, even if you attend online. Dust off your camera, dig out your user manual and get ready to enjoy a new level of fun with photography! You'll use your camera during the workshop to assure you get the most out of the day.

It is recommended that you have a digital camera that allows you to change the exposure settings. Camera phones are not recommended since you don’t have control over the settings.

Sign up now so you can fully understand how your camera works and why your pictures don’t always turn out the way you want.

The workshop will be Loren's studio in downtown Somerville, NJ, just two blocks from the NJ Transit train station. You'll receive detailed directions after you register. For online attendance Loren uses a high quality video conferencing service that allows you to see him and his computer screen while being able to hear everything and ask questions. If your computer doesn't have a microphone, you can use the text function to ask questions. Those attending online will be given detailed instructions on how to join the series via your computer or mobile device.

The workshop will be recorded so if you miss something, you can watch it later online.

May 11 from noon to 5:00 p.m.

$179 Regular registration
$159 for early registration by April 1.
$139 for returning clients and Premium Members

For more information and to register go to https://lorenphotos.com/mevents/novice-photography-bootcamp/

name: Sketching at Leith Harbour.
description:
From the Kings Wark, walk towards the Queens Dock, past the old Signal Tower, (built in 1685) to the Merchant Navy Memorial. On the left, you will see the "seated figure" and the harpoon gun, then proceed to the road bridge. I shall be seated facing the city.

In Greek Mythology, those who drink from the "waters of Lethe" will experience forgetfulness and oblivion.

name: Kensington Derby and Arts Festival
description:
Derby teams construct a human-powered vehicle—no stored energy, motors, or electricity—and travel a 3-mile urban course through Fishtown and East Kensington, complete with obstacles. The Derby parade ends with a final mud pit obstacle in front of the viewing stands and the panel of judges.

The Arts Festival celebrates the incredible mix of local artists, musicians, and eateries in the neighborhood. Held on Trenton Avenue, a wide cobblestone street that has been part of the community's rich creative history for over a hundred years, the festival features over 200 local arts and food vendors.

how_to_find_us: We'll meet inside the pub and have drinks and lunch before heading out.
name: The East End: Maureen Paley, Hollybush Gardens and Campoli Prest!
description:
On the day the Venice Biennale opens its doors, Contemporary Art London explores galleries a little closer to home. And at these three prime East End galleries we'll be exploring the work of artists working predominantly in painting, but also in a range of media.

Hollybush Gardens: Bruno Pacheco: Head (red) Hand
Hollybush Gardens presents head (red) hand, an exhibition of new and recent paintings by Bruno Pacheco that continue the artist’s ongoing enquiry into the painted picture. The exhibition also showcases an extensive selection of works on paper, which have been compiled into books that visitors are encouraged to browse.
http://hollybushgardens.co.uk/?page_id=39

Campoli Presti: Lion Hunt
High-visibility yellow is for maximum retinal stimulation in already hyper-stimulated urban environments. It fights and overwhelms Reena Spaulings’ pigments, sometimes causing strange optical shifts, making certain greens look purple while normally bright and primary yellows become dull like mustard on the anti-colour of the high-viz support.
https://www.campolipresti.com/exhibitions/solo-exhibition-10

Maureen Paley: Garder Ein Einarsson
Maureen Paley is pleased to present the third solo exhibition by Gardar Eide Einarsson at the gallery. The group of work that makes up the show revolves around concerns of how to relate, and how to resist, as an individual in the face of institutions and power structures whose ideologies might not align with ones own.
https://www.maureenpaley.com/exhibitions/gardar-eide-einarsson-1?image=1

Event details:

12:00pm: We'll meet at the The Dundee Arms on Cambridge Heath Road.

13:15pm we'll head to the exhibitions.

14:45pm: If everyone's seen enough we'll head to a nearby pub to catch up on the shows and meet other members.

Before the show:
You'll receive a MeetUps message ahead of the show letting you know on any updates to the event, so make sure you check this before coming along.

What to bring:
A notebook if you want to write down your thoughts.

Preparation:
Extra marks for anyone who does some research on the show/artists before and has any questions they want to bring with them.

Etiquette:
As always, if you can't make it just send a message to let me know and take your name off the RSVP list.

Cost:
CAL doesn't take anything for these events and the exhibitions are free to enter.

Social media:
Taking photos? If you're on Instagram make sure to @contemporaryartlondonevents and/or #CALevents

So RSVP for the event here and via the link and look forward to seeing you there!

name: Swan Falls Picnic and Dam Tour
description: South of Kuna lies Swan Falls Dam on the Snake River. Let's meet in the park at noon for a picnic and social time. Afterward, we can tour the dam itself, hike the dirt road along the river below the dam or just hang out until it's time to call it a day.

name: NZ Portrait Gallery current exhibition and Talk - Haru Sameshima
description:
The Wellington Portrait Photography MUG actively seeks public events that we can attend together.

This talk is the next scheduled for the New Zealand Portrait Gallery and it will be discussing portrait photography with an illustrated talk about documentary and studio photo traditions in New Zealand, and Edith Amituanai's place within both traditions.

Edith Amituanai is one of the photographic artists that is currently featured at the Portrait Gallery and we will view her and George Crummer's work before the talk. Afterwards, let's grab a coffee!

What the Gallery says about the "Edith and George: in our sea of islands" exhibition:

With 100 years separating them, photographers Edith Amituanai (b. 1980 Auckland) and George Robson Crummer (b. 1868 Auckland, d. 1953 Rarotonga) each capture moments in time from their Pacifica communities.
What emerges in the space between these two sets of portraits is a conversation about migration, colonisation, settlement, cross-cultural exchange and identity across the Pacific Ocean.

Please note: The Google address differs from the NZPG website. Google places the gallery at Shed 11 Lady Elizabeth Lane, Wellington.

description:

We can try to do it within two hours. The area provides for many great photo locations and is one of the Tech hubs in London.

Prav

name: Ride/Drive+Camping+BBQ@ Pocharam lake
description:
Event NOTES:

Event Type : Lake side Camping.

WHO can join : Anyone who is sportive, bare the inconvenience of "Travel More" & LOve Being in Nature.

Where : Pocharam Reservoir.

About Place

Pocharam Wildlife Sanctuary is a forest and wildlife sanctuary located 15 km (9.3 mi) from Medak and 115 km (71 mi) from Hyderabad ,Telangana India. Spanning over 130 square kilometres (50 sq mi), in the districts of Nizamabad and Medak it was a former hunting ground of theNizam that was declared a wildlife sanctuary in the early 20th century. It is named after the Pocharam lake formed from the bunding of the Allair from[masked]. The sanctuary has an ecotourism center for visitors. It is home to many species of birds and mammals.

Itinerary:

01:00 PM : Start from Balanagar Cross roads
04:30 PM: Reach Pocharam lake and walk to the camping spot
05:00 PM: Start pitching tents
08:00 PM: Dinner followed by camp fire and sharing travel experiences.
10:00 PM : Night walk if Possible
05:30 AM: Wake-up and witness the emerging colors of dawn.
06:30 AM: Morning walk.
09:00 AM: Start back to Hyderabad
11:00 AM: Bye Bye

What to wear: Wear any thing comfortable. ...

What to bring:

-Packed Dinner from home OR you can buy it in Medak when we halt there.
- Water bottles- 2 x 1 liters
- Trekking shoes (must) and a pair of slippers if needed.
- An extra pair of change of clothes & shorts.
- Sleeping bag if u have one or a thick blanket

name: Glamour! Marilyn Style!  Balance Natural Light & Flash in a Glamour  Setting
description:
Join us on Saturday, May 11 for this super workshop, a glamour style shoot in the spirit of Marilyn Monroe. Like all of our workshops, we don't just set up the lighting, give you the settings and let you fire away. We work on a concept of photography teach the theory behind it and apply it in a hands on method. This workshop will help develop your skills / concept of:

1. Balancing Ambient light with Strobe Lighting (Natural Light vs Flash Light )
2. Watching shadow and light ratios
3. Working with / without a light meter
4. Learn about light ratios, incident and reflected, for great shots
5. White Balance
6. Posing for this glamour / boudoir genre of shoot

While our model ( yet to be decided ) is getting makeup / hair ready, we will discuss the concept and theory of balancing light. Then we will practice what we learned. Always hands on and always informative. Guaranteed to bring your images up a level!!

So, join in on this relaxing and informative Marilyn inspired workshop. Not just learning and not just practice. You will come away with beautiful images for your portfolio as well. Our female model (Yet to be determined ) will have 2 - 3 looks / outfits. • Fresh batteries!

• Your favourite lens;

* In order to trigger the studio strobes, your DSLR camera must have a working flash hot-shoe for the wireless transmitter. If you are not sure, please email me. Sony/Minolta DSLR Owners: Sony uses a proprietary hot-shoe for their cameras; you will need to bring your own hot shoe adapter.

Who should come to this workshop?

• This workshop is perfect for beginners and perfect for photographers who have a basic knowledge of their camera and its manual settings.

name: Nobody Promised You Tomorrow: Art 50 Years After Stonewall
description:
Nobody Promised You Tomorrow: Art 50 Years After Stonewall commemorates the fiftieth anniversary of the 1969 Stonewall Uprising—a six-day clash between police and civilians ignited by a routine raid on the Stonewall Inn, a gay bar in New York City—and explores its profound legacy within contemporary art and visual culture today. The exhibition draws its title from the rallying words of transgender artist and activist Marsha P. Johnson, underscoring both the precariousness and the vitality of LGBTQ+ communities.

The exhibition presents twenty-two LGBTQ+ artists born after 1969 whose works grapple with the unique conditions of our political time, and question how moments become monuments. Through painting, sculpture, installation, performance, and video, these artists engage interconnected themes of revolt, commemoration, care, and desire

This will be a casual photo event with lighting, a model, and some cool gear for you to try. Practice new techniques, try new gear, and have fun!

You'll have the opportunity to test out Panasonic's S1 and S1R full-frame cameras and the brand new Sigma MC-21 Adapter, which allows you to use Sigma Art Canon lenses on the Panasonic S1 and S1R!

The Photo Leaders
Brett Wells - Sigma

Brett Wells has worked in the field of photography for over 20 years. He has a Masters of Art degree in photography from the University of Westminster, London, UK. He taught photography at the Art Institute of Atlanta for 7 years and currently teaches workshops around the United States. His work has been published and exhibited in this country and abroad.

He specializes in outdoor and travel photography, choosing to search out wildlife, wildflowers, landscapes, architecture and people throughout the country and around the world. His workshops reflect this and are often taught in national parks and other natural settings.

Brett is a Technical Representative for Sigma Corporation of America, supporting Sigma, photographers and photographic education around the country. He has been a sales representative for Sigma and other leading photographic manufacturers for 8 years.

Why people are sleeping less and what you can do about it
How you can change your brain with mindfulness and mediation
The research that proves the heart sends more signals to the brain then the brain sends to the heart and why it matters
Top biohacks to calm the nervous system and reduce reactivity

About the speaker:

In his management consulting practice (www.BusinessBrainLLC.com), Elias is finding more and more high performers on the verge of burnout. This has prompted Elias to find new techniques and technologies to empower his clients to reduce stress so they can perform better.

As the organizers of Biohackers LA, and a member of the Biohacking Collective, Elias has access to the leading science of peak performance and will share his top Biohacks for stress reduction.

name: Shooting Basic Video
description:
Before you can attend this Meetup, you must first pay & register here: (https://www.precision-camera.com/shooting-basic-video/)

Video — your camera can shoot it but not sure where to start? Have you tried video but aren't happy with the results? Shutter, ISO, Aperture — don’t work the same as when taking photos. Need help making sense of it?

In this course, we introduce beginner concepts and techniques necessary for shooting video with a DSLR or Mirrorless camera. Targeted at beginning videographers and anyone interested in shooting video, this course covers cinematography basics.

Topics Covered
• Choosing a Camera
• Lens Selection
• Basic Stabilization and Tripods
• Basic Storytelling
• Frame Rates
• Shutter Speed, Aperture, ISO in relation to video
• Resolution
• Basic Audio
• Basic Lighting Considerations
• Basic Concepts of Editing

Required Equipment
• Camera - DSLR or Mirrorless that records video
• A freshly formatted memory card
• A fully charged battery
• Note-taking Supplies
• A tripod (optional)

Audience
This course is geared towards beginners in videography. We also assume you are familiar with your camera and it’s use. The concepts covered assume you are a photographer and requires an understanding of intermediate photography concepts - shutter, ISO, aperture, composition.

Schedule and Format
This is a lecture and hands-on class. The first three hours of class are spent in the Precision Camera classroom covering the concepts outlined above. The last half hour will be spent using your camera to shoot short video clips, try different settings, ask questions and receive one-on-one guidance.

About the Instructor
Todd White specializes in fashion, portrait and commercial photography/videography. He has photographed with many country artists including Carrie Underwood, Luke Bryan, Miranda Lambert and George Strait. A selection of these photos have been published in People and Country Weekly magazines. Other commercial work has been published in Vogue, British Vogue, the Wall Street Journal and Texas Highways. Other commercial clients include Altar'd State, Facebook, Pinterest and Neiman Marcus. Todd has videography and editing experience in fashion and commercial projects. He has shot/edited spots for Austin Area Chevy, The Alamo in San Antonio, City of Georgetown and Rudy's BBQ. He is the Director of Media for Fashion X and Producer and Videographer for the Daytripper TV show on PBS.

name: (Game of Thrones)Dark Glamour -FUNdamental Signature Series lighting workshop
description:
Dark Glamour Photography Fundamentals - A WTPG Signature Series lighting workshop

Dark Glamour - Lighting that not only tells the story but emotes a feeling and mood into the viewer of the image. We will help you create some artfully lit Dark and glamorous images in this small group setting (limited to only 6 participants)

Do you have a Passion for Studio lighting? Do you want to learn to create stunning creative and emotive photographs? This is the lighting workshop you have been waiting for!

We have an amazing young Model Starla gracing us with her presence for this fun lighting workshop. We will have a few awesome outfits to light and shoot during this workshop. This workshop is designed to be a FUN and Educational lighting workshop.

This is the perfect lighting workshop for beginners and still great for the intermediate shooters looking to shoot some great Light. We will discuss our lighting objectives, positioning of lights and types of modifiers typically used to create stunning images and truly emote with light.

Thank you for choosing to support your local photography group!

We are a not for profit corporation thats main goal is reducing the finacial and physical barriers for photographers to explore studio photography. We are doing these workshops to build up the local artistic community not earn profit off of it. We have held over 600 photography workshops in the GTA and we have furnished over 500 completly free workshop spots for the local artists over the past 3 years.We run our workshops to give access to local photographers who don't want to drive downtown to shoot, to inspire,educate and share our passion for photography. We look forward to shooting with you and accompanying you on your creative journey .

- Revprint Studio 205 in Toronto -A efficient 780 sq ft premium Pantograph blackout studio located at 146 Thirtieth Street unit 205 Toronto On equipped with Elinchrom flashes and modifiers and 14 ft ceilings.

We also Subsidize rentals for members of WTPG, only $45 per hr including a lighting tech and equipment (3 hr booking min) Check out the images below of this awesome studio! Perfect for your next creative project or client shoot!

What do we offer from our unpretentious and engaging workshops?

• Time is money, and we want everyone to get the most of their experience! That’s why we hold efficient classes; to allow for short, information packed sessions that maximize the shooting time for each participant. You can buy double shooting time in the workshop just email me for details if your interested.

• A safe and comfortable, yet professional environment for everyone to gather, network, and of course, to take photos!

• An array of light modifiers such as; reflectors, umbrellas, soft-boxes, grids, snoots, and beauty dishes.

• Multiple, quick, one-on-one sessions with the model(s) to optimize your chances of getting that “perfect” shot- No turkey shoots!

“What should I bring to the session?!”

First thing’s first; you need your camera! Any model DSLR camera with a working hot-shoe is perfect! *Fresh batteries! (No one loves a dead battery, YIKES!)Formatted memory cards to ensure you can take as many lovely photos as possible!Your favourite lens; anything from 10mm-200mm will work just fine!Don’t forget to bring your passion for great photography and a thirst for knowledge!We will bring the fun! (WOO HOO!)

Who should take our sessions?

Our sessions are perfect for photographers who have a basic knowledge of their camera and its manual settings (don't worry -we will give you the F-stop and shutter speed for perfect results!). They are also suitable for any level of photographer looking to dive into different styles of photography, learn some great lighting set ups, and have some FUN!

name: Elizabethan Clerkenwell - Shakespeare and his Queen
description:
Treachery and spectacle!

A description that could be applied to Shakespeare's plays or the life of his patron - Queen Elizabeth. Our knowledge of most of the aspects of day to day existence in Elizabethan England is sparse but in 2 particular areas it is rich in detail – theatre and royalty. On this tour we learn all about the upstart playwright's time in Clerkenwell including a stop at the site of a theatre where his plays were performed. We also find out how dangerous life was for Good Queen Bess and visit many outstanding historical buildings, still existing today, that she would have frequented.

Join us to discover the parishes, plays and murderous plots of Elizabethan Clerkenwell.

Cost £10 payable on the day.

For photos of the walk see the album at www.facebook.com/guidetribe

See www.londonguidetribe.com for further walks.

2:30pm: Photographers meetup and have general photography talk/discussion. Get to know studio lighting equipment. Savi Styles will answer your questions about studio lighting. Model should be finishing with the make up artist.

3pm: Three (3) hours open shooting in glamour styles using the studio strobes. The open shooting session will be photographer rotation, not paparazzi style. Limited available photographer signups. This is a shootout so there is no lighting workshop but Savi Styles will explain all of the details of the lighting setup.

6pm: The open shootout session will come to an end.

After the shootout, photographers have the opportunity to shoot One On One with Mikayla for 30 minute sessions. You can shoot various styles of your choice including Glamour, Lingerie, and bikini. ( 1 on 1 Session additional $65 per half hour. (Limited to four (6) 1/2 hour slots))

name: Timelapse Treffen Wien #3
description:
Willkommen zum drittenTimelapse-Treffen in Wien!

Ich bin Matthias Hausdorf, Timelapse Fotograf aus Wien, und möchte euch die Timelapse Fotografie näher bringen.

Wir treffen uns im Stadtpark beim Stadtparksteg (U4 Stadtpark), genauer Punkt auf Google Maps: https://goo.gl/maps/idrBr4tKbZphoxxU7

Das sollte ein schöner Platz sein. Jeder hat die Möglichkeit mit seiner Kamera ein Timelapse aufzunehmen während wir uns über das Thema austauschen und ich euch paar Tipps gebe.

Jeder ist willkommen! Egal ob Hobby Fotograf, der schon mal ein Timelapse aufgenommen hat, ob Profi, mit dem man sich über technische Details unterhält oder auch blutige Anfänger die noch nie ein Timelapse gemacht haben und es lernen möchten.

Ich werde euch für Fragen zur Verfügung stehen, euch Tipps geben und mein Wissen weitergeben - freu mich aber auch das ein oder andere von euch zu lernen :-)

Ich freu mich auf euch! Wenn ihr Fragen habt, schreibt mir einfach 😀
lg Matthias
